.SH NAME
PannerNode \- PannerNode
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[CR]PannerNode\f[R] interface defines an audio\-processing object
that represents the location, direction, and behavior of an audio source
signal in a simulated physical space.
This \f[CR]AudioNode\f[R] uses right\-hand Cartesian coordinates to
describe the source\[cq]s \f[I]position\f[R] as a vector and its
\f[I]orientation\f[R] as a 3D directional cone.
.PP
A \f[CR]PannerNode\f[R] always has exactly one input and one output: the
input can be \f[I]mono\f[R] or \f[I]stereo\f[R] but the output is always
\f[I]stereo\f[R] (2 channels); you can\[cq]t have panning effects
without at least two audio channels!
